    "name": "Hemolysis sensitivity to impeller clearance and rotational speed",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analysis varied impeller tip clearance (±15% of nominal 0.3 mm), inlet flow rate (3–6 L/min), and rotational speed (2000–3500 RPM) across a full-factorial design of 45 CFD runs. Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) exhibited strongest sensitivity to rotational speed (normalized sensitivity index 0.61) and tip clearance (0.38), with flow rate contributing 0.21; interaction effects between speed and clearance accounted for an additional 9% of NIH variance, confirming the model correctly identifies worst-case conditions at high speed and tight clearance."
  },
